PART II - RESPONSIBLE AI LICENSE (RAIL) USE RESTRICTIONS
=============================================================================

In addition to the permissions and conditions stated in Part I, the following
use restrictions apply to this Software, its outputs, and any derivative works.
These restrictions are intended to prevent the repurposing of AI-native
cybersecurity tooling designed to protect critical infrastructure for offensive
use against the very systems it is designed to defend.

You agree NOT to use the Software, or any derivative work, for any of the
following purposes:

1. OFFENSIVE USE AGAINST CRITICAL INFRASTRUCTURE
   Using the Software, its models, outputs, evaluation methodologies, protocol
   specifications, or architectural designs to plan, execute, or assist in
   cyberattacks, intrusions, disruptions, or sabotage targeting industrial
   control systems (ICS), operational technology (OT), manufacturing systems,
   or any critical infrastructure as defined by the Cybersecurity and
   Infrastructure Security Agency (CISA).

2. WEAPONS AND MILITARY TARGETING
   Using the Software to develop, enhance, or deploy autonomous weapons
   systems, military targeting systems, or any system designed to cause
   physical harm to persons or property.

3. SURVEILLANCE AND MONITORING OF INDIVIDUALS
   Using the Software for mass surveillance, unauthorized monitoring of
   individuals, tracking of persons without their informed consent, or any
   application that violates the privacy rights of individuals.

4. VULNERABILITY EXPLOITATION
   Using the evaluation toolkit, adversarial testing methodologies, or
   protocol specifications contained in this Software to discover, develop,
   or weaponize exploits against industrial control systems, OT networks,
   or manufacturing equipment - except for authorized defensive security
   testing conducted with the explicit written consent of the system owner.

5. DECEPTION AND MISINFORMATION
   Using the Software to generate false threat intelligence, fabricated
   incident reports, misleading security assessments, or any output intended
   to deceive operators, analysts, or decision-makers responsible for the
   security of critical infrastructure.

6. DISCRIMINATORY APPLICATIONS
   Using the Software in any application that discriminates against
   individuals or groups based on race, ethnicity, gender, sexual orientation,
   religion, nationality, disability, or any other protected characteristic.

